post_text:
As we prepare for our first day of school tomorrow, we would like to share a few reminders:

Parent drop off will be in the north parking lot. There will be a one-way, drop-off lane.

Only students and staff will be allowed in the building.

If your child is riding bike to school, please visit with them about a safe path to school. Bike racks are located on the south-side of the school by the bus lanes.

We will have additional staff outside to aid students in finding their way to breakfast or their classrooms.

If your child is not riding the bus, please don’t drop them off until 8:05am if at all possible.

Preschool’s first day is Monday, September 21st.

We are really excited to see all of our students. Here’s to a great start to the school year!

post_text:
If you are signed up for Literacy Camp on Monday through Thursday, please follow the directions below:

1. Please drop off your child on the south side of the Ada-Borup High School.
2. The students will enter on the North Side of the school. Door 13 (between the gym and locker rooms). Look for signs.
3. Parents will not be able to enter the building with the students.
4. Temperatures will be taken at the door.
5. Masks are required for all students entering the building.
6. All students must have a liability waiver sheet filled out to attend (staff will have clipboards with forms available).
7. Camp is from 8:30am-11:30am.
8. Students will be walked back to the doorway where they are dropped off.

post_text: Congrats to the Cougar Clay Target Team as they have finished their modified season placing 3rd in their conference. Well done trap shooters!

post_text: Congratulations to Kindlee Christianson on earning gold at the first ever virtual FCCLA National STAR Event competition for her Chapter Service Project Display “We Stand with Yuda Bands”. She went above and beyond polishing her project and competing to a camera instead of live judges.

Football players in grades 9-12. We can use the weight room in groups of 6. Get your group of 6 together and email Coach Tinjum so we can set up a schedule to get everyone in lifting. post_text:
What a great turnout so far this week for 2020 Summer Rec! Registration is still open, come play with us! With respect to all of our safety please limit the number of family members that you are bringing with to practices and please observe social distancing guidelines while you are here at the school.

Here’s to continued beautiful weather and to the hope that we can schedule more activities for our athletes as the summer keeps going! Thank YOU for your support, thank YOU for your help during these times, thank YOU for allowing us to coach your athletes and thank YOU for being the strong community that we can rely on! Play ball!
Your Summer Rec Staff
text:
What a great turnout so far this week for 2020 Summer Rec! Registration is still open, come play with us! With respect to all of our safety please limit the number of family members that you are bringing with to practices and please observe social distancing guidelines while you are here at the school.

Here’s to continued beautiful weather and to the hope that we can schedule more activities for our athletes as the summer keeps going! Thank YOU for your support, thank YOU for your help during these times, thank YOU for allowing us to coach your athletes and thank YOU for being the strong community that we can rely on! Play ball!
Your Summer Rec Staff

post_text:
A Message from Lake Agassiz Regional Library:

Are you ready for a summer of exploration? This year, Lake Agassiz Regional Library's Summer Library Experience will be a little bit different - we're going online! Children from birth to age 13 are invited to join us at larl.org/explore to sign up for an account, track their reading to earn tickets and then enter them into drawings for amazing prizes!

Teens and adults are invited to investigate a museum heist with this year's Mystery Program! Get weekly clues and be the first to solve the mystery of the missing artifact.

Both programs will run from June 15-August 15; more information is available at larl.org/explore.

Video: https://youtu.be/nOJa9D2NQ9M

We'll update you on the status of the trip when appropriate.

post_text: Because of this Covid-19 issue, manufacturers and suppliers have had their schedules and supply chains turned on their head. One such manufacturer is Dean Foods, our milk supplier. Due to staffing issues caused by "social distancing", Dean Foods is only able to produce chocolate 1% and white 1%. As a result, students may not be able to choose the flavor they want, but they WILL have milk.
